      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Garden, ¶ 24 April 1872. ¶  ¶ You have always, noble Sir, taken such a lively interest in anything concerning the fate of Leichhardt ¶  ¶ that I would like to correct a mistaken rece...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">72.04.24b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: 'Erh. 11. Juni 1872' [received 11 June 1872]. For a published version of this letter, see Voigt (1996), pp. 110-11.</p>
               </note>Melbourne im bot Garten</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">24/4/72</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Stets haben Sie, edler Herr, einen so regen Antheil an Allem genommen, das auf Leichhardts Schicksal sich bezog, dass ich Ihnen gegenüber eine irrige Mittheilung aus letzter Zeit berichtigen möchte.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wie Inspector Gilmour mir die vermeintlichen Ziegenhaar Zierrathen von Eyre's Creek brachte, sagte mir selbiger, dass solche in Brisbane sorgfältig verglichen wären. Ich war selbst zur Zeit sehr mit Geschäften bedrängt, und nahm ohne eigen Untersuchung die Mittheilung als eine richtige an. Nachdem ich nun aber selbst einen genauen Vergleich angestellt, finde ich, dass diese Riemen aus den Schweifenden des Perameles Lagotis bereitet sind. Der Beweis von<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Leichhardts Anwesenheit an Eyre’s Creek<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">soweit</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>solcher aus der vermeintlichen Auffindung von Spuren von Ziegen entnommen war, ist nun entkräftet.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Petermann published the preceding paragraph<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>as a footnote to 'J. M. Gilmore's Reisen in Central-Australien zur Aufsuchungvon Spuren Leichhardt's, 1871' [J. M. Gilmore's travels in Central Australia in search of traces of Leichhardt, 1871],<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Petermann's geographische Mittheilungen</seg>, vol. 18 (1872), p. 441.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich habe Briefe von Mr Giles<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>aus dem Innern Südaustraliens. Zwar ist dort die Jahreszeit eine sehr trockne gewesen, indessen schreitet er rüstig vorwärts u ich zweifle nicht dass er sein Ziel, die Küste Westaustraliens in extratropischen Breiten, erreichen wird.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beide Mr Forrest sind verhindert, in diesem Jahr wieder auszugehen, bereiten sich aber für eine neue Inland Reise für den Beginn von 1873 vor. Ich sende Ihnen mit der Buchpost eine neue Karte dieser Herrn.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Botanic Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24 April 1872.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You have always, noble Sir, taken such a lively interest in anything concerning the fate of Leichhardt<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that I would like to correct a mistaken recent communication.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When Inspector Gilmour brought me the artefacts from Eyre's Creek<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>supposedly made of goat's hair, he told me<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that they had undergone a careful comparison in Brisbane.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to A. Petermann, 31 January 1872<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 72-01-31b).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I myself was at the time heavily pressed with work and accepted the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>communication as correct without making a personal examination. But after having<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>now<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>made a careful comparison<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>myself,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I find that these straps were fashioned from the tail ends of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Perameles l</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">agotis</seg>.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Greater Bilby.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>So the proof of Leichhardt's presence at Eyre's Creek, in as far as it was based on the alleged finding of traces of goats, is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>now<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>invalidated.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have letters from Mr Giles<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letters not found. The earliest letter written by Ernest Giles<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in 1872<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that has been found is E. Giles to M, 12 July 1872.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from the interior of South Australia. Although the season has been a very dry one there, he pushes ahead<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vigorously<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and I have no doubt<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that he will attain his goal of reaching the coast of Western Australia in the extra-tropical latitudes.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Both Messrs Forrest<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John and Alexander Forrest.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have been unable to go into the field again this<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>year<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but are preparing for a new expedition into the interior in the beginning of 1873. I am sending you a new map from these gentlemen<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Map shewing the overland tracks from Perth to Eucla &amp; Adelaide by John Forrest, Govt. Surveyor 1870</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(London: John Murray,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1871)? Alexander Forrest was second-in-command of this expedition.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by book post.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
